                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d959">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-02-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that he has been advised by the committee that the governor
                    of Serres reports that Miss Stone has been found at a point not named, and is
                    expected to reach Serres on February 24.)</p>
            </div>
